'''Dafydd ap Bleddyn''' (died 1346) was the [[Welsh people|Welsh]] Catholic Bishop of [[St. Asaph]] in Wales from 1315 to 1346, succeeding Llywelyn ap Llywelyn.

Ap Bleddyn is thought to be a descendent of the 'tribe of [[Hafod Uchtryd|Uchtryd']]. His time as bishop is thought to have been relatively uneventful, and records suggest that he remained mainly within the diocese. He is known to have attended the [[consecration]] of Roger of Lichfield at [[Halesowen]] in [[West Midlands (region)|West Midlands]] in June 1322.

Ap Bleddyn died in 1346, when he was succeeded by John Trevor.
<ref>{{cite web|title=Dafydd ap Bleddyn|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-DAFY-APB-1346.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>

