[[File:Ping Sien Si - 006 Jinzha (16134702152).jpg|250px|thumbnail|right|Jinzha]]

'''Jinzha'''({{zh|c=金吒|p=Jinzha}}) is a figure in [[Chinese mythology]], appearing in works such as ''[[Fengshen Yanyi|Investiture of the Gods]]''. A disciple of the "superiorman" [[Wenshu Guangfa Tianzun]], he is the eldest brother of [[Nezha]] and elder brother of [[Muzha (deity)|Muzha]].

==Character biography==
Jinzha was born to General [[Li Jing (deity)|Li Jing]].{{Sfn|Chew|2002|p=144}} The eldest brother of Nezha and the elder brother of Muzha,{{Sfn|Chew|2002|p=169}} Jinzha has been a disciple of Manjusri Bodhisattva for "many years", who was previously Broad Altruist, or Wenshu Guangfa Tianzun.{{Sfn|Chew|2002|p=168}}

