'''Karram-Allah-u Wajhah''' ({{Lang-ar|'''كرم الله وجهه'''}}; {{Lang-en|'''May God exalt his face'''}}) is almost solely used to honor [[Ali]] as the only early [[Muslim]] who never knelt down to an idol following his guardian and teacher [[Muhammad]] in [[Jahilyah]]. This honorific is mostly used by some [[Sunni]]s and is acceptable to [[Shi'a]]. However, Shi'a prefer using [['Alayh-es-Salam]] or "Peace be upon him."

