{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = Sri | name = Ramesh Puri | honorific_suffix = Maharaj | image = | image_size = 150 | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = Hindi | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name above --> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|06|10}} | birth_place = [[Patne]], [[Malegaon]], [[Maharashtra]], India | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | death_cause = | body_discovered = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} --> | monuments = | residence = Patne | nationality = India | other_names = | ethnicity = <!-- Ethnicity should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | citizenship = Indian | occupation = Hindu preceptor }}
'''Ramesh Puri Maharaj''' (or ''Ramesh Baba'') (born 1960, [[Patne]], [[Maharashtra]] state) is an Indian [[Sant (religion)|sant]]. He was born on [[Vat Purnima|Vat Savitri Purnima day]] (the full moon day in the festival to the goddess [[Savitri and Satyavan|Savitri]]).
== Devotion == Ramesh Puri is a devotee of the divinities ''Bhagwaan Mahadeva'' (the god [[Shiva]] in his dancing pose); ''[[Kartikeya]]'' (son of Shiva); ''[[Dattatreya]]'' (the reincarnation of a trinity of Hindu gods); and ''Gadhad Nath''. He belongs to the Niranjani ''akhada'' (monastery) which honours these divinities.<ref>[http://www.epaper.lokmat.com/bigwin.aspx?url=EpaperImages//Nsk//2572015//d60540-large.jpg&eddate=07/25/2015&pageno=3&edition=45&prntid=37638&bxid=26048384&pgno=3 ''Ramesh Puri.''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925095917/http://www.epaper.lokmat.com/bigwin.aspx?url=EpaperImages%2F%2FNsk%2F%2F2572015%2F%2Fd60540-large.jpg&eddate=07%2F25%2F2015&pageno=3&edition=45&prntid=37638&bxid=26048384&pgno=3 |date=2015-09-25 }} Epaper.lokmat.com (in Hindi) Accessed 25 September 2015.</ref>
== Devotional sites == [[File:Patane JPG2 malegaon.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Shri Kshetra Rameshwar Shivalay Anand Ashram, Patne]] The monastery built the ''Shri Kshetra Rameshwar Shivalay Anand Ashram'' (roughly, the Holy Pilgrims' Rameshwar Shivalay Anand Retreat) which is devoted to Kartikeya and Dattatreya.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ou9cMl24jJA ''Rameshwar Shivalay Anand Ashram, Patne, Malegaon.''] YouTube 15 September 2015. Accessed 25 September 2015.</ref> It is large structure with 51 columns and a height of {{convert|81|ft|m}}. The monastery also built the ''Samadhi temple of Swami Gadhad Nath Maharaj'' (roughly, the Consciousness temple of the Divine Lord Gadhad our teacher).
== Duties == Ramesh Puri is the ''Prabhari'' (caretaker) of the Sarsaiya Ghat under the auspices of the Shivbndhu Services Committee.<ref>[http://www.gangadevdipawalikanpur.org/ghats.php?id=47 ''Sarsaiya Ghat''] Ganga Dev Dipawali. Accessed 27 September 2015.</ref> He also teaches the [[Mudra]] Chikitsha.<ref>[http://oshodhara.org.in/Oshodhara/Scheduleaacharya.php?id=Dr%20Ramesh%20Puri ''Ramesh Puri schedule''] Oshodhara.org Accessed 25 September 2015.</ref>
