'''Sfira''', or '''Mrah Es-Sfire'''   ({{lang-ar|سفيرة}})   is a northern Lebanese [[Sunni Islam in Lebanon|Sunni Muslim]] and [[Maronite]] Christian village.<ref>{{cite web|title=Municipal and ikhtiyariah elections in Northern Lebanon|url=http://www.localiban.org/IMG/pdf/iiMonthly-Municip-Mar10-E92.pdf|publisher=The Monthly|accessdate=20 April 2015|page=23|date=March 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603040803/http://www.localiban.org/IMG/pdf/iiMonthly-Municip-Mar10-E92.pdf|archivedate=3 June 2016|df=}}</ref> It is located in [[Miniyeh-Danniyeh District]] and bounded on the north by [[Kfarbnine]], on the south by [[Beit El faqs]], on the west by the mountain of Sfira and on the east by the western Lebanese chain.

